parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause a range of problems, including loss of power, faulty sensors, and malfunctioning accessories, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Airbag system failures can lead to failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
Throttle body and pedal issues can cause loss of power, hesitation, and stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Transmission and traction control issues can cause loss of power, hesitation, and stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Heating and cooling system issues can cause discomfort, distraction, and loss of visibility, which can lead to accidents.
Ignition and starting system issues can cause the vehicle to fail to start, which can leave the driver stranded.
The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to failure to deploy in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injury or fatality.
